<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="moduleone">
    <title>Module 1: The Invertible Matrix Theorem</title>

    <introduction>
        <p>This module covers the synthesis of matrix invertibility concepts.</p>
    </introduction>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-imt-equivalence">
        <title>Equivalent Expressions</title>
        <p>The Invertible Matrix Theorem gives us many ways of saying the same thing.</p>
    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-imt-composition">
        <title>Invertibility and Composition</title>
        <p>The inverse <m>A^{-1}</m> transforms <m>A\vec{x}</m> back to <m>\vec{x}</m>.</p>
    </subsection>
</section>